-- Target unit to buy back $900 million in notes
-- 
-- Tue Apr 6, 2010 9:41am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/04/06/us-target-idUSTRE6352IN20100406

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Target Corp ( TGT.N ) said on Tuesday that one of its subsidiaries is offering to buy back notes with a principal amount of $900 million issued by its credit card trust. 

 Target Receivables Corp's offer expires at 5 p.m. EDT (2100 GMT) on April 13. The company plans to fund the repurchase with cash it has on hand and will pay par value plus accrued interest. Barclays Capital Inc ( BARC.L ) and J.P. Morgan Securities ( JPM.N ) are the lead managers on the offer. (Reporting by  Phil Wahba , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)